column5: Tuff fishing, 4 guys spent 3 days on the water, morning till dark. We caught a total of 2 Walleye, 4 Sheephead and 1 10lb. Pike. This is one of the Walleye 32 1/4 "   8 Rod spread   14 1/2 Lb. Sheephead, my buddy had a hard time lifting.  Most fish caught between Kieth Shoal and Bat Cave. Our other Buddy's caught 5 Walleye. Their biggest was 32 1/2" All fish were caught trolling. We tried Thompson's Pt. and marked lots of fish. But the guys didn't want to jig, just troll. Next time down in Nov. I'll be jigin. :
You are right Fish Farmer when trolling won't produce then adjust your presentation!
Great report Fish Farmer  ....that is one HUGE sheeeeeeeepy
Great report Fishfarmer.  Sorry the pickerel were not more cooperative, but you got into fish right  Joey
thanks for the report, nice looking eye!
Great report and pics Fish Farmer  Nice looking eye and that sheep is huge Best of luck for next time Thanks for sharing Leechman
I'm sure there were lots of laughs throughout the day to make up for the low fish numbers.!!  Looked like a good outing FF !

Well kudos to you guys,3 days morning till dark !!!   man thats some serious trolling,and even an 8 rod spread,  at least you got a few,it has been a tough fish for a week now...well better luck next time,it will get better !!!   thanks for sharing,and hey at least the sheepie break up the boardom between fish !!!...cheers
aaaaaaa *Thanks* for the good time (Fish--farmer) nice pictures good luck next month when you go again right *farmer--02
Nice Fishing FF ...love them Quinte Reports ...
Real nice report, pics, and fish FF!!!  Who was captain of the boat???... Captain rulez yanno!!!  Make their    walk the plank the next time if they don't want to jig!!!
Dog bite you in the arse again Jed?

Well FF nice to see a report from you very nice eye yes the fishing is slow but the big ones are just starting there fall migration from Lake O.  Terry loves to catch those big sheepies luckily he won't be sliming Wayne's boat with them this year

Great report!!!  A beauty eye and a huge sheepie!  Last time I was at Quinte, I'd have been very happy with just catching the sheepshead!! LOL.  Great to see the big walleye coming in....always love this time of year for those monster eye reports....

Thanks guys, and Joey. I hate to say Joey, I was the net man  OH I forgot camera man to.  I left the catching for the other guys I'll be back Nov 21,22,23 to kick We stay at the Picton Harbor Inn,10 in our group, may see some of you there.
